{"nodes":[{"id":"964ddbce","parent_ids":[],"kind":"OBSERVE","content":"Existing blog posts in docs/blog/ follow a consistent template (header, deck, OG meta, JSON-LD). Index lives at docs/blog/index.html and lists post cards + JSON-LD blogPost entries. Sitemap lives at docs/sitemap.xml.","timestamp":"15:03:15"},{"id":"a007d209","parent_ids":["964ddbce"],"kind":"OBSERVE","content":"CVE-2025-59536: <1.0.111, CWE-94, fix in 1.0.111 (Oct 3 2025). Trust dialog bypass — code in untrusted dir executed before dialog accepted. Reporter: avivdon (HackerOne).","timestamp":"15:03:15"},{"id":"957974cf","parent_ids":["a007d209"],"kind":"OBSERVE","content":"CVE-2026-33068: <2.1.53, CWE-807, fix in 2.1.53 (Mar 18 2026). .claude/settings.json with permissions.defaultMode=bypassPermissions silently skipped trust dialog. Reporter: Cantina.","timestamp":"15:03:15"},{"id":"8ed6425f","parent_ids":["957974cf"],"kind":"THINK","content":"Plan: write two technical posts. (1) cve-2025-59536-startup-trust-dialog.html — explains the trust-dialog code-injection bug, why agentic CLIs need trust gates, what changed in 1.0.111. (2) cve-2026-33068-bypass-permissions-settings.html — explains how repo-controlled settings.json fed into the trust gate (CWE-807), recommended posture (don't commit bypassPermissions, review .claude/ before first open), pin to 2.1.53+. Both posts: factual, link to NVD + GHSA, credit reporters, tie back to h5i provenance/audit where natural without overclaiming. Then update docs/blog/index.html (cards + JSON-LD), docs/sitemap.xml, and the JSON-LD in docs/index.html if it lists posts.","timestamp":"15:03:22"},{"id":"2332488d","parent_ids":["8ed6425f"],"kind":"ACT","content":"wrote docs/blog/cve-2025-59536-startup-trust-dialog.html","timestamp":"15:05:42"},{"id":"5c63090e","parent_ids":["2332488d"],"kind":"ACT","content":"wrote docs/blog/cve-2026-33068-bypass-permissions-settings.html","timestamp":"15:07:13"},{"id":"409a1a15","parent_ids":["5c63090e"],"kind":"ACT","content":"e